data.content:
noun
plural ~ goals
[count] chiefly Brit :a goal in soccer, hockey, etc., that a player accidentally scores against his or her own team
We lost the game when one of our players scored an own goal for the other team.
Brit :something that you do because you think it will help you but that actually hurts you
The workers scored an own goal by demanding such high wages that no one could afford to employ them.

Danh từ
(thể thao)
bàn do cầu thủ đội nhà ghi vào khung thành nhà
